<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="514" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,582,1651]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,266,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Diagnosis</emphasis>
. Tergites 
<number box="[380,423,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
with basal subrectangular and apical transversal brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[1143,1229,582,607]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1197,1229,582,607]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
); hypandium with long bristles at apex (
<figureCitation box="[392,477,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[445,477,618,643]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
); phallus with large dorsal subapical appendix in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[1182,1264,618,643]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1235,1264,618,643]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
) and spiniform projections laterally, best visualized in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[742,826,654,679]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[794,826,654,679]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="514" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,582,1651]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,337,690,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[352,413,690,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Male</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[429,514,690,715]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[482,514,691,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[534,598,690,715]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Head</emphasis>
: Face parallel-sided, dark brown with gray pruinescence visible in ventral view, about 
<date box="[291,326,727,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<number box="[291,305,727,751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="4.0">4</number>
X
</date>
longer than lower width. Ocellar tubercle protuberant, dark brown with gray puinescence; ocelli yellow. Scape and pedicel yellow with yellow bristles; postpedicel brown about 
<date box="[1087,1121,763,787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<number box="[1087,1100,763,787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than pedicel; stylus about 
<date box="[220,254,799,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<number box="[220,233,799,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="2.0">2</number>
X
</date>
longer than postpedicel. Proboscis yellow shorter than head height. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[1018,1107,798,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Thorax</emphasis>
yellow, shiny (
<figureCitation box="[1278,1362,798,823]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1330,1362,799,823]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="47.0">47</number>
</figureCitation>
). Legs yellow, except for hind femur and tibia with black apical ring and all tarsomeres 
<number box="[1077,1119,834,859]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="4.5" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="4.0">4–5</number>
black; hind tibia and tarsus with anterodorsal and posterodorsal rows of longer bristles. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[898,963,870,895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Wing</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[988,1078,870,895]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1049,1078,871,895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="48.0">48</number>
</figureCitation>
) hyaline, pterostigma brown, conspicuous, about 
<number box="[386,420,906,931]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="2.5">2.5</number>
X longer than wide. Halter yellow. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[856,972,906,931]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Abdomen</emphasis>
yellow, shiny; tergites 
<number box="[1259,1301,906,931]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
with basal subrectangular and apical transversal brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[743,880,942,967]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Figs 49, 50</figureCitation>
); tergite 
<number box="[985,999,943,967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two subrectangular plates; sternite 
<number box="[240,254,979,1003]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="8.0">8</number>
divided in two trapezoidal plates. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[637,778,978,1003]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Terminalia:</emphasis>
Anterior cercus with a reclinate dorsal projection in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[220,350,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Figs 49, 51</figureCitation>
), subrectangular in dorsal view (
<figureCitation box="[717,801,1014,1039]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[769,801,1014,1039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
); descendant plate subtrapezoidal in posterior view (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,183,1050,1075]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Posterior cercus with rounded apex in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[836,979,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Figs 49, 51</figureCitation>
); without dorsal projections (
<figureCitation box="[1333,1424,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1050,1075]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="52.0">52</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypoproct suboval in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[546,627,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,627,1086,1111]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
) and comma-shaped in posterior view (
<figureCitation box="[1070,1154,1086,1111]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1122,1154,1086,1111]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="53.0">53</number>
</figureCitation>
). Epandrial with bilobate ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[303,437,1122,1147]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Figs 49, 51</figureCitation>
); spiniform bristles mesially on dorsal lobe and longer bristles apically on ventral lobe (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,243,1158,1183]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="51.0">51</number>
</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium longer than wide, with truncate apex and median sinus, with long bristles at apex (
<figureCitation box="[1339,1424,1158,1183]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1392,1424,1158,1183]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
). Phallus with narrower base, extending towards the apex, longer than hypandrium, with a larger dorsal subapical appendix in lateral view (
<figureCitation box="[456,542,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[513,542,1230,1255]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="55.0">55</number>
</figureCitation>
) and spiniform projections laterally in ventral view (
<figureCitation box="[1175,1264,1230,1255]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1232,1264,1230,1255]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
). Subepandrial sclerite wider than long, V-shaped (
<figureCitation box="[546,630,1266,1291]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[598,630,1266,1291]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). Bacilliform sclerite without folds and longer than subepandrial sclerite (
<figureCitation box="[159,244,1302,1327]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[212,244,1302,1327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="54.0">54</number>
</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[263,459,1302,1327]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Specimen length</emphasis>
