<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="514" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,582,1651]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1518,1543]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[324,703,1518,1543]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Opeatocerata" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chaetohypandrialis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[324,703,1518,1543]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[713,804,1518,1543]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[713,804,1518,1543]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
differs from other species by the following characters: tergites 
<number box="[240,282,1554,1579]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="4.5" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="3.0">3–6</number>
with basal subrectangular and apical transversal brown spots (
<figureCitation box="[986,1068,1554,1579]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[1039,1068,1554,1579]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="50.0">50</number>
</figureCitation>
) (other species have paramedian spots on the tergites); hypandrium with bristles at apex (
<figureCitation box="[779,860,1590,1615]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[831,860,1590,1615]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="57.0">57</number>
</figureCitation>
) (other species without bristles on the hypandium); phallus with spiniform projections laterally (
<figureCitation box="[650,731,1626,1651]" captionStart="FIGURES 47 – 57" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1814,1837]" captionTargetBox="[151,1417,194,1792]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[151,1436,193,1794]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 47 – 57. Opeatocerata chaetohypandrialis sp. nov., holotype ♂. 47. habitus, lateral view; 48. wing; 49. abdomen from tergite 4 to terminalia, lateral view; 50. tergites 3 – 8, dorsal view; 51. terminalia, lateral view; 52. lobes of cerci, dorsal view; 53. descendant plate of anterior cercus and hypropoct, posterior view; 54. subepandrial sclerite and bacilliform sclerite, dorsal view; 55. ejaculatory apodeme, phallus and hypandrium, lateral view; 56. apex of phallus, ventral view; 57. hypandrium, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/252526/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="514">
Fig. 
<number box="[702,731,1626,1651]" pageId="12" pageNumber="514" value="56.0">56</number>
</figureCitation>
) (in other species without spiniform projections laterally).
</paragraph>
